  "prompt": "What are the recipes of five minutes easy to make snacks?",
  "response": "Okay, here are five super easy snack recipes you can whip up in five minutes or less:\n\n**1.  Peanut Butter Banana Bites**\n\n*   **Ingredients:**\n    *   1 Banana, sliced into 1/2-inch thick rounds\n    *   2 Tablespoons Peanut Butter (or almond butter, sunflower seed butter, etc.)\n    *   Optional Toppings: Chocolate chips, chopped nuts, shredded coconut, sprinkles\n\n*   **Instructions:**\n    1.  Spread a small amount of peanut butter on each banana slice.\n    2.  Top with desired toppings (or just eat them plain!).\n\n*   **Why it's quick:**  It's literally just slicing, spreading, and sprinkling!\n\n**2.  Avocado Toast with Everything Bagel Seasoning**\n\n*   **Ingredients:**\n    *   1 Slice of Toast (whole wheat, sourdough, etc.)\n    *   1/4 Avocado, mashed\n    *   Everything Bagel Seasoning\n    *   Optional: Red pepper flakes, squeeze of lemon juice, salt/pepper to taste\n\n*   **Instructions:**\n    1.  Toast the bread to your liking.\n    2.  Mash the avocado and spread it on the toast.\n    3.  Sprinkle generously with Everything Bagel Seasoning.\n    4.  Add optional toppings if desired.\n\n*   **Why it's quick:** Toasting and mashing are the only real \"cooking\" steps.\n\n**3.  Yogurt Parfait**\n\n*   **Ingredients:**\n    *   1/2 Cup Yogurt (Greek, regular, plant-based)\n    *   1/4 Cup Granola\n    *   1/4 Cup Berries (fresh or frozen)\n    *   Optional: Honey or maple syrup for a touch of sweetness\n\n*   **Instructions:**\n    1.  Layer yogurt, granola, and berries in a glass or bowl.\n    2.  Repeat layers if desired.\n    3.  Drizzle with honey or maple syrup (optional).\n\n*   **Why it's quick:**  It's all about layering ingredients you already have.\n\n**4.  Caprese Skewers**\n\n*   **Ingredients:**\n    *   Cherry Tomatoes\n    *   Small Fresh Mozzarella Balls (Bocconcini)\n    *   Fresh Basil Leaves\n    *   Balsamic Glaze (optional)\n\n*   **Instructions:**\n    1.  Thread a cherry tomato, mozzarella ball, and basil leaf onto a small skewer or toothpick.\n    2.  Repeat until you have the desired number of skewers.\n    3.  Drizzle with balsamic glaze (optional).\n\n*   **Why it's quick:**  No cooking required, just assembly.\n\n**5.  Quick Quesadilla**\n\n*   **Ingredients:**\n    *   1 Tortilla (flour or corn)\n    *   1/4 Cup Shredded Cheese (cheddar, Monterey Jack, etc.)\n    *   Optional: Salsa, cooked chicken or beans, veggies\n\n*   **Instructions:**\n    1.  Sprinkle cheese (and any optional fillings) onto one half of the tortilla.\n    2.  Fold the other half of the tortilla over the cheese.\n    3.  Microwave for 30-60 seconds, or until the cheese is melted.  Alternatively, heat in a dry skillet over medium heat for 1-2 minutes per side until golden brown and cheese is melted.\n    4.  Cut into wedges and serve.\n\n*   **Why it's quick:**  Microwaving or a quick skillet cook makes it ready in seconds.\nEnjoy your speedy snacking!  Let me know if you'd like some more ideas!\n",
